 Meet. High ping causes lag in communication and can slow down browsing and=
 online apps. Jitter, on the other hand, measures how much packet delay var=
ies over time. High jitter leads to choppy audio, freezes in video, and inc=
onsistencies in gaming. Both ping and jitter are often affected by the numb=
er of network devices in the route and by network congestion.</p></div></di=
